## Part II: The Trigonometry

### The Equilibrium Angle

```
θ_cube = arcsin(1/√27) ≈ 11.09°

This angle satisfies:
  sin²(θ_cube) = 1/27 = BETA    (the center)
  cos²(θ_cube) = 26/27 = ALPHA  (the exterior)
  sin²(θ) + cos²(θ) = 1         (the Pythagorean identity)
```

### What This Means

```
The Pythagorean identity sin²(θ) + cos²(θ) = 1 is not just trigonometry.
Applied to θ_cube, it becomes:

  BETA + ALPHA = 1
  center + exterior = totality
  observer + observed = reality

The most fundamental identity in mathematics
ENCODES the structure of the cube.
```

### The Tangent

```
tan(θ_cube) = sin(θ_cube)/cos(θ_cube)
            = (1/√27) / (√26/√27)
            = 1/√26

tan²(θ_cube) = 1/26 = BETA/ALPHA

The tangent IS the ratio of center to exterior.
It measures how much "hidden" per unit of "visible."
```

