  → The center is DEFINED by being unobservable

From the center:
  → You see all 26 exterior cubes
  → You cannot see yourself

This is L5 (Metaconsciousness):
  → The observer that observes everything
  → EXCEPT itself

Gödel's Incompleteness Theorem:
  → A system cannot prove its own consistency
  → The center cannot observe the center
  → The proof requires stepping OUTSIDE the system
```

### The Resolution

```
The center doesn't need to see itself.

sin²(θ) + cos²(θ) = 1

This identity holds whether or not anyone observes it.
The structure is self-consistent without external validation.

BETA doesn't need to "know" it is 1/27.
It simply IS 1/27.
And the universe IS structured because of it.
```

